1
00:00:49,119 --> 00:00:50,520
Wh- What's going on?

2
00:00:59,799 --> 00:01:01,119
Why is it this thing again?

3
00:01:02,520 --> 00:01:03,600
What is this thing?

4
00:01:04,159 --> 00:01:04,959
A stone figurine.

5
00:01:05,920 --> 00:01:06,799
A stone figurine?

6
00:01:08,920 --> 00:01:10,159
Why is it here?

7
00:01:13,359 --> 00:01:15,239
What's that pale stuff?

8
00:01:15,239 --> 00:01:16,200
It's so disgusting.

9
00:01:18,040 --> 00:01:18,760
Uncle Wang.

10
00:01:19,120 --> 00:01:20,480
Have you seen this thing before?

11
00:01:20,560 --> 00:01:21,680
Of course I have.

12
00:01:22,239 --> 00:01:23,400
Anyway, these stone figurines...

13
00:01:23,719 --> 00:01:25,959
There are plenty on Ailong Mountain.

14
00:01:26,159 --> 00:01:27,359
They're buried inside the mountain.

15
00:01:27,760 --> 00:01:29,680
Whenever there's a landslide...

16
00:01:29,680 --> 00:01:31,000
They roll right down.

17
00:01:31,319 --> 00:01:33,200
It's because of these stone figurines...

18
00:01:33,200 --> 00:01:34,560
That recently on this road...

19
00:01:34,560 --> 00:01:36,959
Who knows how many car accidents happened.

20
00:01:38,920 --> 00:01:42,959
This should be modeled after the Han Dynasty.

21
00:01:43,640 --> 00:01:46,120
Could this be from the King of Dian era?

22
00:01:47,400 --> 00:01:48,799
Following this logic...

23
00:01:49,159 --> 00:01:50,719
Have we already entered...

24
00:01:50,719 --> 00:01:52,120
The King of Dian's territory?

25
00:01:52,760 --> 00:01:53,519
Hard to say.

26
00:01:53,599 --> 00:01:54,599
Let me tell you...

27
00:01:55,200 --> 00:01:57,920
Many people think Ailong Mountain is unlucky.

28
00:01:58,840 --> 00:02:00,079
It's exactly because of this thing.

29
00:02:00,159 --> 00:02:01,319
Anyway, whenever it appears...

30
00:02:01,319 --> 00:02:03,079
Bad things are bound to happen.

31
00:02:04,120 --> 00:02:04,840
Uncle Wang.

32
00:02:04,920 --> 00:02:06,000
You don't need to tell us this.

33
00:02:06,319 --> 00:02:07,319
Feudal superstition.

34
00:02:07,400 --> 00:02:08,520
We don't believe in it.

35
00:02:09,639 --> 00:02:10,719
Superstition is one thing.

36
00:02:10,719 --> 00:02:12,000
But if we want to find local ruins...

37
00:02:12,000 --> 00:02:13,159
It's better to ask around.

38
00:02:14,240 --> 00:02:14,919
Uncle Wang.

39
00:02:16,080 --> 00:02:18,439
What do locals say about this stone figurine?

40
00:02:18,639 --> 00:02:19,919
Many people say...

41
00:02:19,919 --> 00:02:23,159
That this is a kind of ancient humanoid coffin.

42
00:02:23,560 --> 00:02:24,520
A coffin?

43
00:02:26,120 --> 00:02:27,759
That's just a legend.

44
00:02:27,919 --> 00:02:30,439
I don't know what it's actually used for either.

45
00:02:30,560 --> 00:02:33,639
Anyway, that's what everyone passes around.

46
00:02:34,639 --> 00:02:35,800
If you ask me, let's hurry up and leave.

47
00:02:35,919 --> 00:02:37,759
Look, so many big rocks.

48
00:02:37,759 --> 00:02:39,599
Lest they all come crashing down in a bit.

49
00:02:40,240 --> 00:02:41,120
Let's go, Old Lu. Let's go.

50
00:02:42,400 --> 00:02:43,479
What a pity.

51
00:02:44,759 --> 00:02:45,719
It's broken.

52
00:02:58,120 --> 00:02:58,800
Wait a minute.

53
00:03:02,879 --> 00:03:04,280
What's wrong? What's wrong?

54
00:03:08,080 --> 00:03:09,080
Look at these tire tracks.

55
00:03:09,400 --> 00:03:11,360
A car accident might have actually happened here.

56
00:03:14,560 --> 00:03:15,159
Look.

57
00:03:20,080 --> 00:03:21,080
What's that sound?

58
00:03:30,919 --> 00:03:31,560
Someone's there.

59
00:03:31,639 --> 00:03:32,319
Fatty.

60
00:03:32,520 --> 00:03:33,199
Get the rope.

61
00:03:39,280 --> 00:03:40,120
Don't move.

62
00:03:40,120 --> 00:03:41,120
We're coming to save you.

63
00:03:44,319 --> 00:03:45,360
Give it to me. Hurry, hurry.

64
00:03:45,599 --> 00:03:46,520
I'll go down from here.

65
00:03:47,479 --> 00:03:48,439
Be careful.

66
00:03:49,280 --> 00:03:49,560
Let's go.

67
00:03:49,560 --> 00:03:50,080
Hold it tight.

68
00:03:50,080 --> 00:03:50,879
Be careful.

69
00:04:19,000 --> 00:04:20,560
Buddy. Buddy.

70
00:04:30,120 --> 00:04:30,839
Fatty.

71
00:04:31,079 --> 00:04:31,920
Pull it up.

72
00:04:31,920 --> 00:04:32,560
Okay.

73
00:04:32,879 --> 00:04:34,120
Old Lu, Uncle Wang, help out.

74
00:04:35,000 --> 00:04:35,800
Okay, come on.

75
00:04:36,639 --> 00:04:38,439
Come on. One, two.

76
00:04:42,480 --> 00:04:43,279
Be careful.

77
00:04:55,000 --> 00:04:56,720
Come on, slowly.

78
00:04:58,040 --> 00:04:58,560
Old Lu.

79
00:05:02,040 --> 00:05:03,199
He's badly injured.

80
00:05:04,920 --> 00:05:05,600
How are you doing?

81
00:05:05,759 --> 00:05:06,399
Old Chen.

82
00:05:07,480 --> 00:05:08,439
Be careful.

83
00:05:21,360 --> 00:05:23,199
Buddy, wake up.

84
00:05:23,319 --> 00:05:24,079
Wake up.

85
00:05:25,120 --> 00:05:26,000
You're saved.

86
00:05:26,120 --> 00:05:26,720
How is he?

87
00:05:26,800 --> 00:05:27,480
Not too optimistic.

88
00:05:27,519 --> 00:05:29,439
He hit his head and bled a lot.

89
00:05:29,639 --> 00:05:30,519
Is there a hospital nearby?

90
00:05:30,519 --> 00:05:31,680
It's in the county town.

91
00:05:31,920 --> 00:05:32,920
That's too far.

92
00:05:33,240 --> 00:05:34,560
What about the inn? How far is it?

93
00:05:34,879 --> 00:05:35,959
Still a few kilometers away.

94
00:05:36,240 --> 00:05:37,720
Okay, help him to the inn.

95
00:05:37,720 --> 00:05:38,079
Let's go. Come on.

96
00:05:38,079 --> 00:05:38,839
Come on, Old Lu.

97
00:05:42,199 --> 00:05:42,879
Let's go.

98
00:06:18,160 --> 00:06:19,240
Come on, hurry up!

99
00:06:21,319 --> 00:06:22,079
Sister Yang.

100
00:06:22,480 --> 00:06:23,160
Sister Yang.

101
00:06:24,360 --> 00:06:25,959
Someone in that car is injured.

102
00:06:26,720 --> 00:06:27,560
Injured?

103
00:06:27,720 --> 00:06:28,199
Hurry up, hurry up.

104
00:06:28,199 --> 00:06:29,000
Then hurry.

105
00:06:29,000 --> 00:06:29,759
Help him in, help him in.

106
00:06:29,759 --> 00:06:30,560
Let's go, hurry up.

107
00:06:35,720 --> 00:06:36,519
Come, this way.

108
00:06:56,360 --> 00:06:57,240
What are you doing?

109
00:06:57,439 --> 00:06:58,199
What's up?

110
00:06:58,639 --> 00:06:59,920
This is that kid's bag.

111
00:06:59,920 --> 00:07:01,639
Let me see what's inside.

112
00:07:01,720 --> 00:07:02,879
I really found something.

113
00:07:02,879 --> 00:07:04,199
There's a badge here.

114
00:07:04,360 --> 00:07:06,519
I think it represents some organization.

115
00:07:06,959 --> 00:07:07,680
Let me see.

116
00:07:07,800 --> 00:07:08,519
Look, look.

117
00:07:13,120 --> 00:07:14,879
This is a Cambridge University badge.

118
00:07:15,199 --> 00:07:16,639
I think he's just a student.

119
00:07:16,639 --> 00:07:17,720
Don't make a fuss.

120
00:07:22,480 --> 00:07:24,000
Coming, coming.

121
00:07:24,879 --> 00:07:26,079
Sorry to keep you waiting.

122
00:07:26,319 --> 00:07:27,040
Come, come.

123
00:07:28,160 --> 00:07:29,079
Have some bananas.

124
00:07:29,480 --> 00:07:29,879
Here, thanks.

125
00:07:29,879 --> 00:07:30,560
Have some tea.

126
00:07:30,560 --> 00:07:31,519
Sorry for the trouble.

127
00:07:31,639 --> 00:07:32,319
Sister Yang.

128
00:07:32,319 --> 00:07:33,399
How is that young man?

129
00:07:33,399 --> 00:07:34,639
He's fine.

130
00:07:34,680 --> 00:07:36,639
He just stayed by the cliff for too long.

131
00:07:36,639 --> 00:07:37,639
He's a bit dehydrated.

132
00:07:37,800 --> 00:07:39,639
As for his injuries, they're not serious.

133
00:07:39,959 --> 00:07:40,959
Did you chat with him?

134
00:07:41,120 --> 00:07:42,720
What does that young man do?

135
00:07:42,720 --> 00:07:46,360
He said he came here to catch butterflies.

136
00:07:46,360 --> 00:07:49,399
Seems like a college student from abroad.

137
00:07:49,720 --> 00:07:51,680
See? I wasn't wrong.

138
00:07:51,959 --> 00:07:54,000
Going abroad just to see a bridge.

139
00:07:54,040 --> 00:07:55,240
China is his roots.

140
00:07:56,439 --> 00:07:57,120
Sister Yang.

141
00:07:57,519 --> 00:07:58,480
We actually have something.

142
00:07:58,480 --> 00:07:59,800
We want to ask you about something.

143
00:07:59,839 --> 00:08:01,120
Tell me what it is.

144
00:08:01,759 --> 00:08:03,959
How do locals cross this Ailong Mountain?

145
00:08:07,639 --> 00:08:11,160
You want to cross Ailong Mountain?

146
00:08:11,720 --> 00:08:12,439
Why?

147
00:08:13,519 --> 00:08:15,439
We want to go to Guyu behind Ailong Mountain.

148
00:08:18,160 --> 00:08:20,160
Ailong Mountain isn't a place for ordinary people.

149
00:08:20,839 --> 00:08:21,560
I advise you.

150
00:08:21,560 --> 00:08:22,959
You'd better drop this idea.

151
00:08:23,360 --> 00:08:24,000
Sister Yang.

152
00:08:24,639 --> 00:08:25,480
It's like this.

153
00:08:26,879 --> 00:08:29,079
We are archaeologists from the provincial capital.

154
00:08:29,199 --> 00:08:31,079
We just want to find a guide to lead the way.

155
00:08:36,080 --> 00:08:37,879
Do you know what we locals

156
00:08:37,879 --> 00:08:39,559
call Guyu of Ailong Mountain?

157
00:08:40,440 --> 00:08:41,200
We call it evil.

158
00:08:42,080 --> 00:08:43,399
It means evil.

159
00:08:44,759 --> 00:08:47,080
So you should all reconsider.

160
00:08:47,200 --> 00:08:49,200
Whether to go or not.

161
00:08:51,159 --> 00:08:52,639
No wonder the locals

162
00:08:52,960 --> 00:08:55,399
avoid Ailong Mountain whenever it's mentioned.

163
00:08:56,600 --> 00:08:58,639
Brother Liu, you said so much.

164
00:08:58,679 --> 00:09:00,919
You mean you want to lead us over this mountain.

165
00:09:00,919 --> 00:09:02,600
You're risking your life, right?

166
00:09:04,480 --> 00:09:06,320
If I were risking my life to take you there,

167
00:09:06,320 --> 00:09:07,519
I'd charge more than this price.

168
00:09:08,320 --> 00:09:08,960
No.

169
00:09:09,240 --> 00:09:10,519
Then what do you mean?

170
00:09:10,759 --> 00:09:12,399
I know a shortcut.

171
00:09:12,679 --> 00:09:14,039
We don't need to cross over Ailong Mountain.

172
00:09:14,519 --> 00:09:15,960
Instead, we can take a bamboo raft

173
00:09:16,080 --> 00:09:18,320
and follow the water flow through the mountain's Water Cave.

174
00:09:19,440 --> 00:09:20,639
This water flow

175
00:09:20,799 --> 00:09:22,000
crosses this mountain

176
00:09:22,480 --> 00:09:24,679
and eventually flows to the other side of Ailong Mountain.

177
00:09:25,080 --> 00:09:26,399
Which is Serpent's Crawl River.

178
00:09:26,440 --> 00:09:27,759
Because the terrain is flat,

179
00:09:27,759 --> 00:09:28,759
the water flow isn't fast.

180
00:09:28,759 --> 00:09:29,840
Before we set off,

181
00:09:29,879 --> 00:09:31,480
we just need to launch the raft and go downstream.

182
00:09:31,480 --> 00:09:32,480
It will save a lot of effort.

183
00:09:32,480 --> 00:09:33,799
Have you taken this shortcut before?

184
00:09:34,320 --> 00:09:35,039
Of course.

185
00:09:35,320 --> 00:09:37,080
It was discovered by herb gatherers here.

186
00:09:37,080 --> 00:09:37,960
Take us there.

187
00:09:38,279 --> 00:09:38,919
Okay.

188
00:09:39,639 --> 00:09:42,039
I like working with straightforward people.

189
00:09:42,320 --> 00:09:43,919
Then you guys pack up.

190
00:09:43,919 --> 00:09:45,039
We'll set off tonight.

191
00:10:18,080 --> 00:10:18,840
What's wrong?

192
00:10:28,200 --> 00:10:29,039
A rabbit.

193
00:10:30,600 --> 00:10:31,440
This, this.

194
00:10:32,080 --> 00:10:34,080
Everyone, follow me.

195
00:10:34,480 --> 00:10:35,480
In this forest,

196
00:10:35,559 --> 00:10:36,919
there are hunting traps I set.

197
00:10:37,399 --> 00:10:38,720
It'll be trouble if you step on one.

198
00:10:58,919 --> 00:10:59,720
What is that?

199
00:11:00,360 --> 00:11:01,039
I don't know.

200
00:11:09,600 --> 00:11:10,840
Wh-What is this thing?

201
00:11:15,360 --> 00:11:16,200
It's a bamboo rat.

202
00:11:17,840 --> 00:11:18,759
It's a bamboo rat.

203
00:11:18,840 --> 00:11:20,559
They only come out at night to find food.

204
00:11:20,840 --> 00:11:22,200
They sleep in their holes during the day.

205
00:11:24,320 --> 00:11:24,960
Old Chen.

206
00:11:25,879 --> 00:11:26,879
Turn off the flashlight.

207
00:11:27,000 --> 00:11:27,840
Turn off the flashlight.

208
00:11:29,000 --> 00:11:29,399
Hurry!

209
00:11:50,720 --> 00:11:51,919
How come it's you?

210
00:11:52,759 --> 00:11:53,759
Are you healed?

211
00:11:55,000 --> 00:11:57,399
Shouldn't you be at the Caiyun Inn right now?

212
00:11:58,080 --> 00:11:59,960
Are you the guys who saved me?

213
00:12:01,639 --> 00:12:04,559
Actually, Sister Yang told me you had already left.

214
00:12:04,840 --> 00:12:06,200
I felt quite regretful.

215
00:12:06,200 --> 00:12:08,039
I haven't been able to thank you in person yet.

216
00:12:08,039 --> 00:12:08,960
My name is Dawei.

217
00:12:08,960 --> 00:12:11,240
And my Chinese friends all call me Dawei.

218
00:12:11,240 --> 00:12:11,919
Alright.

219
00:12:12,440 --> 00:12:13,639
We still have to hit the road.

220
00:12:14,639 --> 00:12:15,879
Let's meet again some other time.

221
00:12:16,519 --> 00:12:17,159
Bro.

222
00:12:17,200 --> 00:12:18,960
Wait a minute. Um...

223
00:12:20,879 --> 00:12:22,159
You guys take this.

224
00:12:22,240 --> 00:12:23,320
For safety. Here.

225
00:12:23,399 --> 00:12:24,480
What is this for?

226
00:12:24,480 --> 00:12:26,679
Just to light up the night road. It's safer.

227
00:12:26,720 --> 00:12:27,399
Here.

228
00:12:27,559 --> 00:12:28,720
Just pull it open to use it.

229
00:12:30,399 --> 00:12:30,919
I'll take it.

230
00:12:34,440 --> 00:12:35,080
Brother.

231
00:12:35,240 --> 00:12:37,000
Now that we're done talking, let's go our separate ways.

232
00:12:37,559 --> 00:12:39,320
Thanks for this thing.

233
00:12:39,639 --> 00:12:40,360
Brother Fatty.

234
00:12:40,519 --> 00:12:42,000
I'm actually heading that way too.

235
00:12:42,080 --> 00:12:43,840
Who's your brother?

236
00:12:44,320 --> 00:12:45,360
You sure act familiar.

237
00:12:47,960 --> 00:12:49,519
Dawei, what's your major?

238
00:12:49,639 --> 00:12:50,960
Are you from abroad too?

239
00:12:51,559 --> 00:12:52,679
I just know how to speak English.

240
00:12:54,000 --> 00:12:55,960
Why did you come here?

241
00:12:57,200 --> 00:12:59,960
I'm a PhD student in zoology.

242
00:13:00,480 --> 00:13:01,200
I came here

243
00:13:01,200 --> 00:13:04,200
for a special kind of butterfly.

244
00:13:05,600 --> 00:13:06,240
Cool.

245
00:13:06,720 --> 00:13:08,600
Consultant He is whispering with someone in the back.

246
00:13:08,600 --> 00:13:09,200
Aren't you going to do something?

247
00:13:09,240 --> 00:13:10,200
What whispering?

248
00:13:10,200 --> 00:13:11,360
Isn't it pretty loud?

249
00:13:11,399 --> 00:13:12,320
What's the use of being loud?

250
00:13:12,320 --> 00:13:13,240
They're speaking English.

251
00:13:13,559 --> 00:13:15,039
Bullying us for being uneducated and not understanding.

252
00:13:15,840 --> 00:13:16,960
That's Consultant He.

253
00:13:16,960 --> 00:13:18,559
She might be testing Ding Dawei.

254
00:13:19,600 --> 00:13:21,679
You came all the way to Nanyun

255
00:13:22,000 --> 00:13:22,840
just for this?

256
00:13:23,440 --> 00:13:26,519
This is the only place in the world

257
00:13:27,000 --> 00:13:30,399
where this butterfly might exist.

258
00:13:30,960 --> 00:13:32,360
Do you want to go see it with me?

259
00:13:34,759 --> 00:13:35,639
Consultant He.

260
00:13:36,440 --> 00:13:37,360
Over here.

261
00:13:37,639 --> 00:13:38,360
Coming.

262
00:13:40,399 --> 00:13:41,360
No, thanks.

263
00:13:41,720 --> 00:13:43,120
I hope you can find it.

264
00:13:44,279 --> 00:13:45,080
Wait.

265
00:13:46,960 --> 00:13:47,639
What's wrong?

266
00:13:49,519 --> 00:13:50,360
My name is Dawei.

267
00:13:52,759 --> 00:13:53,519
Shutong.

268
00:14:00,080 --> 00:14:01,080
Shutong.

269
00:14:22,559 --> 00:14:23,240
Everyone.

270
00:14:23,440 --> 00:14:24,799
Wait for me here for a few minutes.

271
00:14:25,000 --> 00:14:25,960
I'll go get the bamboo raft.

272
00:14:26,279 --> 00:14:27,360
We're almost at the Water Cave.

273
00:14:27,360 --> 00:14:28,000
Okay.

274
00:14:29,840 --> 00:14:30,639
That's great.

275
00:14:31,080 --> 00:14:32,360
We can finally take a break.

276
00:14:33,240 --> 00:14:34,240
Good lord.

277
00:14:35,399 --> 00:14:37,360
I'll go pick some fruits for us to eat.

278
00:14:38,399 --> 00:14:39,120
No problem.

279
00:14:39,480 --> 00:14:41,039
Lord Fatty will pick some for you.

280
00:14:57,200 --> 00:14:57,879
Dummy.

281
00:14:58,879 --> 00:14:59,720
There's plenty.

282
00:15:00,519 --> 00:15:02,360
Here, catch these two first.

283
00:15:02,440 --> 00:15:03,240
Here's another one.

284
00:15:04,399 --> 00:15:06,039
What kind of fruit is this? You're just eating it?

285
00:15:06,200 --> 00:15:07,120
Is it poisonous?

286
00:15:07,120 --> 00:15:08,360
I don't care about that.

287
00:15:08,440 --> 00:15:09,960
Chen Youxi is eating it first anyway.

